INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2455,'If you remember, Monday was an exceedingly hot day, and Mrs. St.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2456,'Clair walked slowly, glancing about in the hope of seeing a cab, as she did not like the neighborhood in which she found herself.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2457,'While she was walking in this way down Swandam Lane, she suddenly heard an ejaculation or cry, and was struck cold to see her husband looking down at her, and, as it seemed to her, beckoning to her from a second-floor window.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2458,'The window was open, and she distinctly saw his face, which she describes as being terribly agitated.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2459,'He waved his hands frantically to her, and then vanished from the window so suddenly that it seemed to her that he had been plucked back by some irresistible force from behind.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2460,'One singular point which struck her quick feminine eye was that, although he wore some dark coat, such as he had started to town in, he had on neither collar nor necktie.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2461,'[Illustration: AT THE FOOT OF THE STAIRS SHE MET THIS LASCAR SCOUNDREL.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2462,']  Convinced that something was amiss with him, she rushed down the steps—for the house was none other than the opium den in which you found me to-night—and, running through the front room, she attempted to ascend the stairs which led to the first floor.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2463,'At the foot of the stairs, however, she met this Lascar scoundrel of whom I have spoken, who thrust her back, and, aided by a Dane, who acts as assistant there, pushed her out into the street.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2464,'Filled with the most maddening doubts and fears, she rushed down the lane, and, by rare good-fortune, met, in Fresno Street, a number of constables with an inspector, all on their way to their beat.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2465,'The inspector and two men accompanied her back, and, in spite of the continued resistance of the proprietor, they made their way to the room in which Mr. St.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2466,'Clair had last been seen.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2467,'There was no sign of him there.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2468,'In fact, in the whole of that floor there was no one to be found, save a crippled wretch of hideous aspect, who, it seems, made his home there.');
