INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2524,'Clair through the window, there is no human eye which could have seen the deed.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2525,'What would he do then? It would of course instantly strike him that he must get rid of the tell-tale garments.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2526,'He would seize the coat, then, and be in the act of throwing it out, when it would occur to him that it would swim and not sink.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2527,'He has little time, for he has heard the scuffle down-stairs when the wife tried to force her way up, and perhaps he has already heard from his Lascar confederate that the police are hurrying up the street.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2528,'There is not an instant to be lost.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2529,'He rushes to some secret horde, where he has accumulated the fruits of his beggary, and he stuffs all the coins upon which he can lay his hands into the pockets to make sure of the coat’s sinking.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2530,'He throws it out, and would have done the same with the other garments had not he heard the rush of steps below, and only just had time to close the window when the police appeared.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2531,'It certainly sounds feasible.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2532,'Well, we will take it as a working hypothesis for want of a better.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2533,'Boone, as I have told you, was arrested and taken to the station, but it could not be shown that there had ever before been anything against him.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2534,'He had for years been known as a professional beggar, but his life appeared to have been a very quiet and innocent one.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2535,'There the matter stands at present, and the questions which have to be solved—what Neville St.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2536,'Clair was doing in the opium den, what happened to him when there, where is he now, and what Hugh Boone had to do with his disappearance—are all as far from a solution as ever.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2537,'I confess that I cannot recall any case within my experience which looked at the first glance so simple, and yet which presented such difficulties.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2538,'While Sherlock Holmes had been detailing this singular series of events, we had been whirling through the outskirts of the great town until the last straggling houses had been left behind, and we rattled along with a country hedge upon either side of us.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2539,'Just as he finished, however, we drove through two scattered villages, where a few lights still glimmered in the windows.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2540,'We are on the outskirts of Lee, said my companion.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2541,'We have touched on three English counties in our short drive, starting in Middlesex, passing over an angle of Surrey, and ending in Kent.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2542,'See that light among the trees? That is ‘The Cedars,’ and beside that lamp sits a woman whose anxious ears have already, I have little doubt, caught the clink of our horse’s feet.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2543,'But why are you not conducting the case from Baker Street? I asked.');
INSERT INTO sentences VALUES(2544,'Because there are many inquiries which must be made out here. Mrs. St.');
